{
  "texts": [
    "LLMs are generally fine-tuned using Parameter Efficient Fine Tuning (PEFT) methods.",
    "Existing PEFT techniques typically fall into three categories (Han et al., 2024): (1) Additive methods (these involve the inclusion of a small set of additional trainable parameters/modules, e.g., Adaptors (Houlsby et al., 2019), Prefix-tuning (Li and Liang, 2021));",
    "(2) Selective methods (these involve selecting a smaller subset of parameters/modules (e.g., bias in the case of BitFit (Ben Zaken et al., 2022)) and fine-tuning only those (via application of binary masks), e.g., Diff pruning (Guo et al., 2021));",
    "(3) Re-parametrization techniques (these involve re-parameterization of existing weight update matrix via low-rank approximation, e.g., LoRA (Hu et al., 2022)).",
    "In this paper, we focus on reparameterization-based approaches."
  ]
}